1. d4
{ Here we're going to look at all the 1...d5 lines where Black tries to develop the light-squared bishop outside the pawn chain and how to react. }
1... d5 2. Bf4 Nf6
{ 2...Nc6  Chigorin  3.e3  Bf5   3...Nf6  4.Nf3  Bg4  5.c4  4.c4   2...Bf5  Baltic. We react with.  3.c4!  For an explanation why, seeChapter 12.   2...c6  3.e3  Bf5  4.c4   2...Bg4?!  Here we react with f3.  3.f3 }
3. e3 c5
{ If  3...Bf5  4.c4   If  3...Bg4  4.Qd3!  with the idea of  Qb3  and  c4 } 4.
Nf3 Nc6 5. Nbd2 Bf5
{ 5...Bg4  6.c3  e6  7.Qa4  Here we play the reversed Cambridge Springs. SeeChapter 5. }
6. dxc5 e6 7. Nd4 Bxc5
{ Black is forced to give up the bishop pair. Any other move and we play Bb5 and b4.   7...Bg6?  8.Bb5  Rc8  9.b4  Be7  10.Nxc6  bxc6  11.Ba6 }
8. Nxf5 exf5 9. c3 { SeeChapter 5. } *

