[Result "*"]

1. d4 d5 2. Bf4 c5 3. e3 cxd4 4. exd4 Nc6 5. c3 Bf5 6. Nd2 e6 7. Ngf3 Nge7
{ Another option is to go for the immediate ...Nge7. This is very unlikely with only 38 games in the database. }
8. Nh4 { This seems best. The alternative is   8.Qb3  followed by Nh4. } 8...
Ng6 { Black attacks our bishop. } 9. Nxf5
{ Exactly 1  (!)  Lichess game has reached here. } 9... Nxf4 10. Ne3 g6
{ This might be Black's best move. If  10...Bd6  11.g3  Ng6  12.Bd3  and White's doing well with the better placed pieces and  f4  possible to clamp down on  e5 }
11. g3
{ Kicking away the knight. However, White has no intention to fianchetto the bishop! }
11... Nh5 12. Bd3
