[Result "*"]

1. d4
{ This was a Classical game. One of our heroes, Sedlak, was rated 2523 while Black was rated 2552. }
1... d5 2. Nf3 Nf6 3. Bf4 c5 4. e3 Nc6 5. Nbd2 e6 6. c3 cxd4 7. exd4 Nh5 8. Be3
Bd6 9. Ne5 g6 10. g4 Ng7 11. h4 h5
{ This is the ...h5 line we will look at next. This game is meant to serve as inspiration. }
12. Bg5 Be7 13. Bxe7
{ A much stronger move and Sedlak's own recommendation in his book is 13. Bb5, which is also our choice. }
13... Qxe7 14. Bb5
{ Sedlak puts pressure on the c6 knight and makes sure the strong e5 knight gets to stay where it is. }
14... O-O 15. Bxc6 bxc6 16. Rg1 { 16.gxh5  Nxh5  17.Rg1 } 16... Qxh4 17. Ndf3
{ 17.Qf3  Was even stronger with a quick O-O-O. } 17... Qf6
{ 17...Qh3  Black had to keep his Queen in White's camp to keep messing with his coordination. However, that is a hard thing to do, when it is in danger of getting trapped. }
18. Qd2 hxg4 19. Rxg4 { White's completely winning already. } 19... Nf5 20.
O-O-O Qh8 21. Rdg1 { Now White can just sacrifice on g6. } 21... Rb8 22. Rxg6+
fxg6 23. Rxg6+ Ng7 24. Rh6
{ The Queen is trapped and after Qxh6, Qxh6, White can just bring in the other knight and mate soon. }
