1. d4 d5 2. Bf4 Nf6 3. e3 c5 4. Nf3 Nc6 5. Nbd2 cxd4 6. exd4 Bf5 7. Bb5 Qb6
{ Second most common move @@StartBracket@@~27 games@@EndBracket@@. This was also played in the stem game Vitiugov - Harikrishna, 2020. }
8. c4 { Fire on the board. } 8... dxc4 9. a4 e6 10. Nxc4
{ 10.O-O  Vitiugov played this and now it's equal after...  10...Bd3 } 10...
Bb4+ 11. Bd2 Bxd2+ 12. Qxd2 Qc7 13. Qb4
{ Preventing castling and threatening Nd6+. } 13... Rd8 14. O-O
{ White's position is much easier to play with all the dynamics favoring him. }
