1. d4 d5 2. Bf4 Nf6 3. e3 c5 4. Nf3 Nc6 5. Nbd2 cxd4 6. exd4 Qb6 7. Nb3 Bg4 8.
h3 Bh5 { It is better for Black to retreat the bishop. } 9. a4
{ Again, the same a4 to a5 to a6 idea. } 9... a6
{ As we know, Black must stop the march of the a-pawn. } 10. a5
