[White "5. The Tricky 4...Qb6?!, 5...Bf5, 5...Bg4"]
[Black "3...Nc6, 4...Qb6, 5...Nf6?"]
[Result "*"]

1. d4 d5 2. Bf4 c5 3. e3 Nc6 4. Nf3 Qb6 5. Nc3
{ Attacking d5 and threatening Nb5. All natural moves lose to one of these threats. }
5... Nf6
{ Natural, protecting d5, but bad due to Nb5. Similarly, if  5...e6?  ,  6.Nb5! }
6. Nb5 e5 { Black is forced to give up a pawn. } 7. Nxe5 a6
{ Black attacks the knight and thinks it will save him but... } 8. Nc4
{ The important move, clearing the way for the bishop's control of c7 with tempo. }
8... dxc4 9. Nc7+ Ke7 10. Nxa8 Qxb2 11. Be2
{ Making room for the king in case of ...Qc3+. } 11... Qc3+ 12. Kf1 cxd4 13.
Rb1
{ Putting pressure on the b-pawn, enabling the knight to escape to b6, and making it harder for Black to develop the light-squared bishop. White is basically winning. }
