1. d4 d5 2. Bf4 c5 3. e3 Nc6 4. Nf3 Qb6 5. Nc3 Qa5
{ This is Stockfish's choice, pinning the knight, but if moving the Queen again is best then you know something must've gone wrong for Black... }
6. dxc5
{ White is ahead in development, grabs a pawn and can hope to hold on to it by a3 and b4. He's also currently attacking d5. }
6... Nf6
{ Protecting the d-pawn and threatening  Ne4  . If instead  6...e6  7.a3  with b4 next. }
7. Bb5
{ White is better. Let's look at one continuation  7...Ne4  8.Qxd5  Nxc3  9.Bxc6+  bxc6  10.Qxc6+  Bd7  11.Qxa8+  and White wins, so Black has to take it more slowly with something like ...e6 and White can continue with a3. }
