1. d4 d5 2. Bf4 c5 3. e3 Nf6 4. Nf3 Qb6
{ Here Black tries to combine ...Nf6 with a quick ...Qb6. } 5. Nc3
{ Again, this is strongly met with Nc3. Nb5 is still a threat, even though the d5-pawn is protected. }
5... Qxb2 { Natural, but poor, due to... } 6. Nb5 Na6 7. a3
{ Strongest, trying to get the Queen into trouble.  7.Rb1  Qxa2  8.Ra1  Qb2  9.Rxa6  bxa6  10.Nc7+  is a good and easy-to-remember forcing alternative which we will look at next. }
7... Bf5
