8. dxc5 { Grabbing a pawn, but also opening up d4 for the b5-knight. } 8...
Bxc2 { 8...Qxc2  9.Qxc2  Bxc2  10.Rc1  transposes. } 9. Qc1 Qxc1+ 10. Rxc1 Bf5
{ Black retreats here since White's basic threat is the immediate c6. For example  10...Bg6  11.c6!  bxc6  12.Rxc6   Or  10...Bg6  11.c6!  b6  12.c7!  are both crushing.   Similarly, if  10...Be4  11.c6! }
11. Nbd4 { Threatening Nxf5, Bb5+ and c6. White is already winning. } *

