{ This novel move, simply stopping Nb5, was repeatedly tried by Nakamura in his match against Carlsen. It's been tried slightly less than 400x. After this play resembles more that of the next chapter on the sharp 5...Qb6 than this one.   5...Bg4  This clearly can't work.  6.Nb5  Na6  7.dxc5!  Qxc5  8.c3±  e6?  A very natural move.  9.Qa4  Due to the discovered checks, White is just winning, for example  9...Nd7  10.Ne5  Nb6  11.Nd6+  Ke7  12.Qd4  Qxd4  13.exd4  Kxd6  14.Nxf7+ }
6. dxc5 { You will see this a lot both in this and the next chapter. } 6...
Qxc5 { Only 20 games have reached here. } 7. Nd4
{ The most interesting idea, intending Ncb5 and forcing ...Na6 as a response. It also makes possible Nb3, chasing the Queen. }
7... e6
