{ Black's only move not to lose. Played 111 times. Of course, this is also Logozar's recommendation. }
8. Nxf5 exf5
{ Logozar's trainable lines actually stop here which is far too soon for a proper evaluation. }
9. c3 { Better than alternative tries like  9.Nb3  . } 9... Bd6
{ One possible move, trying to split the bishop pair into half. It's almost never seen in practice though because simplifications favor White here due to Black's structural weaknesses. }
10. Bg5
{ Switching the diagonal and pinning the knight. White wants to exchange the bishop for the knight to further accentuate the weakness of the d5-pawn. }
10... O-O 11. g3
{ White is playing against the IQP and has ample time to fianchetto the bishop like in the main line of the Tarrasch Defence. }
11... Be7 12. Bxf6 { Yep, we really want this knight. } 12... Bxf6 13. Bg2
{ The IQP is a big target and Black doesn't really have any dynamics favoring him. }
