{ Sedlak and Stockfish give this as Black's best move, after which it is equal. It is the second most common move.  However, practically White still scores well from here. }
8. Nxf3 a6
{ Preventing Bb5. Black could also play  8...c4  with the same idea. However, this is only the 4th most common move here.   Most common is ...Bd6, but  8...Bd6?  9.Ba6!!  works again and other moves can be met with Bb5. }
