Qd7
{ Several GM's have chosen this move in this position. The point is to play ...Bd6 and ...O-O-O. }
9. h3 { Sticking with the program. } 9... Bh5 10. g4 Bg6 11. dxc5
{ Shimanov's and later also Tikkanen's choice, the point is to play O-O-O. }
11... Bxc5 12. O-O-O { Shimanov's choice. } 12... O-O-O
{ Black plays it safe. } 13. Nxg6
{ Shimanov went for  13.Bb5  . Sedlak recommends this move instead which was played by Tikkanen. What follows is a sample line you don't need to commit to memory, but just understand. }
13... hxg6 14. g5
{ If  14...Nh5  15.Bh2  Bd6  16.Bxd6  Qxd6  17.Be2  followed by h4 or the immediate  17.h4  and Black's knight is out of play.   If  14...Ng4!?  15.Ne4!  Qe7  16.Bb5  Nge5  17.Nxc5  . }
14... Ne8 15. c4 Bd6 16. Bxd6 Qxd6 17. Bg2 Nc7 18. Kb1
{ It's +/=, but White's g2-bishop is the best minor piece on the board. } *

