10. Qa4
{ White wants to play Ne5 next. Black has too many options here to continue learning, but to give you a taste what might happen, here are a few lines:   10...Qd7  11.b5  Nb8?  12.Bxb8!  A typical move  Rxb8  13.Ne5  With tempo  Qd6  14.b6+  Another tempo  Nd7  15.bxa7  Ra8  16.Ndf3  White is completely winning here.   10...Qd7  11.b5  Nd8  12.Ne5  Again, White is much better. }
