1. d4 d5 2. Bf4 Nf6 3. e3 c5 4. Nf3 Nc6 5. Nbd2 Qb6 6. dxc5 Qxb2
{ Black's best move. } 7. Rb1 Qxa2
{ This is far too greedy, but has been played ~400x. Similarly bad is  7...Qa3  since it does nothing to stop c4. }
8. Bb5 Bd7
{ Most common. If  8...e6  which is the second most common  9.Nb3!!  and Black's Queen is never getting out. Here's a funky line where Black tries to use the only square available  9...Qa3  10.Qd4!  Qa6  11.Qd3  Qa3  12.O-O  and Ra1 to Ra4 comes next and the Black Queen is lost   If  8...a6  9.Bxc6  bxc6  10.O-O  and White will try to trap the Queen as well. }
9. c4 { Striking at the centre. Also ok is starting with  9.O-O } 9... e6
{ If  9...a6  10.Ba4  e5  11.Bxc6  Bxc6  12.Nxe5 } 10. O-O
{ Completing development. } 10... Bxc5 { Most common. } 11. Nb3 Bb4
{ Retreating to  e7  loses the Queen on the spot  11...Be7?  12.Ra1 } 12. Bxc6
{ Removing the defender of e5. } 12... Bxc6 13. Ra1
{ Everything comes with tempo. } 13... Qb2 14. Be5 Bc3 15. Rb1
{ Black is going to lose something. } 15... Bxe5
{ Objectively best. If  15...Qa3  16.Bxc3  and White is up a piece. } 16. Rxb2
Bxb2 17. Na5 { White will take on c6 and d5 with a nice advantage. } *

