Bb5 Qxc5 { Second most common move with slightly over 200 games. } 9. O-O
{ Completing development and getting the king to safety first! } 9... e6 10. c4
{ The typical break. Black has a variety of moves here. } 10... Bd7
{ One possible move. This is not good, but White needs to know what to do. }
11. cxd5 exd5
{ If  11...Nxd5?  12.Ne4  and White is winning. For example  12...Qa3  13.Nfd2!  threatening Nc4  13...Nc3  14.Nxc3  Qxc3  15.Ba4!   If  11...Qxd5  12.Bc4  and wherever the Queen goes White has Rxb7 next }
12. Ba4
{ Again, the bishop retreat. In this case the idea is Rb5 next. For example  12...Be7  13.Rb5  Qa3  14.Nb1  Qxa2  15.Rxb7  Rc8  16.Nc3  with threats all over the place. }
