Bb5 Qxc5 9. O-O e6 10. c4 Bd6 { Another option. } 11. cxd5
{ Again, principled and easy-to-remember. } 11... exd5
{ If  11...Nxd5??  12.Ne4  wins on the spot. } 12. Rc1
{ An important move, trading the light-squared bishop for the dark-squared one. }
12... Qxb5 13. Bxd6
{ White's down a pawn, but winning since Black won't be able to castle. White can continue with Qc2, a4, and if the bishop is threatened, retreat it to a3. }
