1. d4 d5 2. Bf4 Nf6 3. e3 c5 4. Nf3 Nc6 5. Nbd2 Qb6 6. dxc5 Qxb2 7. Rb1 Qc3 8.
Bb5 Qxc5 9. O-O e6 10. c4 Be7 { The best move. } 11. Nb3
{ Attacking the Queen and preparing to jump to d4, putting pressure on the pinned knight. }
11... Qa3 { If  11...Qb6?  12.Nbd4  . } 12. Nbd4 { Pressure on the knight. }
12... O-O
{ The best move, giving back the pawn and sacrifcing the exchange. If  12...Bd7?  13.Ne5!  Nxe5  14.Bxe5  and White will win material. }
13. Nxc6 bxc6 14. Bxc6 Ba6 15. Bxa8 Rxa8 { If  15...Bxc4?  16.Bb7 } 16. Qc2
dxc4 17. Rb8+
{ The best move, exchanging a pair of rooks and activating the dark-squared bishop. Also possible is  17.e4  , controlling the d5-square. }
17... Rxb8 18. Bxb8 Nd5 19. Be5
{ Putting the bishop on the long diagonal and intending Rb1 with back rank threats or Bb2 next. }
