Bb5 e6 9. O-O Be7 10. e4 O-O 11. e5 Nd7 12. Nb3
{ Protecting c5 and preparing Bd2, trapping the queen. } 12... Qb4
{ A hard move for Black to find. If  12...Bxc5  13.Bd2   Or  12...Nxc5  13.Bd2  and the Queen is trapped.   If  12...Ncxe5  13.Nxe5  Nxe5  14.Bd2  Nf3+  15.Qxf3  Qxf3  16.gxf3  and White is up a piece. }
13. Nbd4 { Protecting the bishops. } 13... Qxc5 14. Re1
{ Protecting  e5  . White could win a pawn with  14.Nxc6  bxc6  15.Be3  Qa3  16.Bxc6  but this doesn't amount to much after  16...Rb8  . }
14... Nxd4 15. Nxd4 a6 16. Bd3 { Returning to the kingside. } 16... g6
{ Obviously Black can't take the knight due to  16...Qxd4  17.Bxh7+  . The text blocks the diagonal and renews the attack on the knight. }
17. Nf3
{ This is Lc0's move. Alphazero played  17.Nb3  instead. The latter move allows the Queen to join the attack faster while our move allows the knight to participate. In both cases the plan is h4-h5 and attack the king. }
