Bb5 g6 9. e4 dxe4 10. Be5
{ There's only one game in the Lichess database that has reached this position. }
10... Qa5 { Shankland's move. } 11. O-O
{ White sacrifices a piece for time. In the database game White played the inferior  11.Nd4  but still won. }
11... exf3
{ White has two options here: Qxf3 and Bxc6. The first leads to a draw by repetition which is good to know, if you need it. The second sets Black lots of practical problems and allows for several different ways of playing. }
