1. d4 d5 2. Bf4 Nf6 3. e3 c5 4. Nf3 Nc6 5. Nbd2 e6 6. c3 Be7 7. Ne5
{ The most precise move, avoiding  7.Bd3  Nh5  , but it's been played only in 1000 games. Here Black can castle or go  ...Nxe5  immediately. }
7... Nxe5 { The second most common option with ~300 games. } 8. dxe5 Nd7 9. h4
{ Offering a poisoned pawn and preparing Qg4 without having to worry about ...g5 and ...h5, e.g.   9.Qg4?  g5  10.Bg3  h5 }
9... Bxh4
{ Black doesn't have to take it, of course.   If  9...O-O  10.Bd3  .  We'll look at the strongest move, 9...c4, next. }
10. Qg4 g5 11. Rxh4 gxh4 12. Qg7 Rf8 13. Bg5 Qb6 14. O-O-O
{ White's basically winning due to the threats of Bxh4 followed by Qg5, Ne4 to Nd6+ and Rd6. }
