Nd7 9. Ndf3 Ndxe5 { The master-level preference and a natural move. } 10. dxe5
{ White could also try  10.Nxe5  , but the text is more thematic. } 10... f6
{ One option. } 11. h4 fxe5 { Taking with the pawn allows for the Greek Gift. }
12. Bxh7+ Kxh7 13. Ng5+
{ This is actually a highly atypical London Gift since the Queen doesn't come directly to h5. }
13... Kg6
{ Black's extra option. It's worse than ...Kg8, but more interesting. If  13...Kg8  14.Qh5  Bxg5  15.hxg5  Rf5  16.g4!  and White will win. }
14. h5+ Kf5 15. Nf7
{ An amazing mating net idea, taking away f7 from the king with an attack on the Queen }
15... Rxf7 { Engines actually just recommend giving up the Queen. } 16. g4+ Kf6
17. g5+ Kf5 18. Rh4
{ Controlling the fourth rank. This is useful after something like Qf3, ...exf4, Qxf4#. }
18... d4 19. Qf3 Qd5 20. Qh3+ Ke4 21. f3+ Kd3 22. Qf1+ Kc2 23. Rh2# *

