1. d4 d5 2. Bf4 Nf6 3. e3 c5 4. Nf3 Nc6 5. Nbd2 e6 6. c3 Be7 7. Ne5 O-O 8. Bd3
Nxe5 9. dxe5 Nd7 10. h4 c4 11. Bxh7+ Kxh7 12. Qh5+ Kg8 13. Nf3 f6 14. Ng5 fxg5
15. hxg5 Bxg5 16. Bxg5 Qb6 17. O-O-O Nxe5 { Perhaps the better try. } 18. Qh7+
{ The engines don't find this by themselves. Thanks, Darkestnight! } 18... Kf7
19. Rh6 { Threatening Rf6+! } 19... Qc7
{ If  19...Qc5  20.Rdh1  Ke8  21.Qxg7  Nf7  22.Rf6  Nxg5  23.Rxf8+  Qxf8  24.Rh8  Qxh8  25.Qxh8+  Kd7  26.Qg7+  Kd6  27.Qxg5 }
20. Rf6+ Ke8 21. Rxf8+ Kxf8 22. Bf4 b6 23. Qh8+ Kf7 24. Qh5+ Kf8 25. Bxe5
{ Material is finally equal, but White is much better due to the weak Black king. He can continue by activating the rook via d4 and f4. }
