1. d4
{ This was a Classical game at the Chess Olympiad in Baku. One of our heroes, the world champion, was rated 2857, Black was rated 2566. }
1... d5 2. Nf3 Nf6 3. Bf4 e6 4. e3 Bd6 5. Bg3 c5 6. c3 Nc6 7. Nbd2 Bxg3 8. hxg3
Qd6 9. Bb5 Bd7 10. Bxc6 Bxc6 11. Ne5 Qc7
{ This is a slightly surprising move. } 12. Qf3 { 12.g4! } 12... h6 13. Qf4
{ Making space for the knight. } 13... Qe7 14. g4 Nh7 15. Qg3
{ Preparing to meet ...Ng5 with f4. } 15... Rg8 16. O-O Nf6 17. Rac1
{ 17.dxc5  Qxc5  18.c4!  White tries to break open the center and has a huge edge. }
17... Rc8 18. c4
{ The break comes now. Black's king is not happy in the center. } 18... dxc4
19. dxc5 Qxc5 20. Ndxc4 Ke7 21. b4
{ 21.Nxf7!  Kxf7  22.Nd6+  With a discovery on the Queen! } 21... Qxb4 22. Nd3
Ne4 23. Nxb4 Nxg3 24. fxg3
{ Black just loses a piece. Carlsen has tripled g-pawns and an isolated e-pawn, but is just completely winning. }
24... Bb5
{ Black might've been relying on this pin, but he missed the following tactic. }
25. Rxf7+ Kxf7 26. Nd6+ Ke7 27. Nxc8+ Kd7 28. Nxa7 Ba4 29. Nd3 *

