{ I like this rare, thematic and straightforward move the best @@StartBracket@@~400 games@@EndBracket@@. The main and most common move is Ne5 and even though White gets an edge, but the lines get quite complex for such a rare line. }
8... Bd7
{ Perhaps the best defense and the second most common move and the main move at master level.   8...a6?  This allows White to demonstrate his thematic idea against Black's soon-to-be damaged Queenside pawns.  9.Bxc6+  bxc6  10.Qa4  Attacking the b-pawn.  10...Bb7  11.Bxd6  We exchange the bishop since we want the Queen to come on d6, unprotected.  11...Qxd6  12.Qa3  Nd7  13.Nb3  White will win a clean pawn.   8...O-O  This is the most common move, but doesn't work either.  9.Bxc6  bxc6  10.Qa4  Bxg3  Black takes so as to avoid the above pattern.   10...Bb7  11.Bxd6  Qxd6  12.Qa3  Same pattern as before.  11.hxg3  cxd4  Black takes, before White gets to pin the pawn.  12.cxd4  Here we take with the c-pawn, aiming to attack Black's backward pawn with moves like Ne5, Rc1, Nb3 etc.   8...Nd7  This doesn't make a ton of sense.  9.O-O  Bxg3  10.hxg3  O-O  11.Re1  To meet ...e5 with e4.  11...e5  12.e4 }
