9. Ne5 { We play the Pillsbury move, blocking  e5 } 9... Bxe5
{ Most common move at both amateur and master level so we'll take this as our main line. Black has many legal moves here, but most of them can be met with thematic play f4, Bh4, O-O etc.   9...Qc7  Second most common move.  10.f4  Nd7??  A very common blunder and it's good to have seen this trap.   10...b6  11.Bh4  The bishop has done its job and its frequently best to switch it to a different diagonal  11...Be7  12.O-O   10...Ne7  11.O-O  11.Bxh7+  Kxh7  12.Qh5+  Kg8  13.Qxf7+  Kh7  14.Qh5+  Kg8  15.Qxe8+  Kh7  16.Qg6+  Kg8  17.Qxe6+ }
