1. d4 d5 2. Bf4 Nf6 3. e3 c5 4. Nf3 Nc6 5. Nbd2 e6 6. c3 Bd6 7. Bg3 O-O 8. Bd3
Re8 9. Ne5 Bxe5
{ Most common move at both amateur and master level so we'll take this as our main line. Black has many legal moves here, but most of them can be met with thematic play with f4, Bh4, O-O etc. }
10. dxe5 Nd7 11. Nf3
{ f4 can be played, but if Black responds correctly it gets quite tricky. White will castle next and play the typical London game. A good thing to know is that ...Qc7 doesn't allow Black to take the pawn due to the threat of Qh5 e. g.  11...Qc7  12.O-O  Ncxe5  15.Nxe5  Nxe5  16.Qh5!  and White is winning. }
