1. d4 d5 2. Bf4 Nf6 3. e3 c5 4. Nf3 Nc6 5. Nbd2 e6 6. c3 Bd6 7. Bg3 O-O 8. Bd3
Qe7
{ The third most popular move in this position  (~4000 games)  . The idea is to push ...e5. }
9. Ne5 { No surprises here. } 9... Bxe5
{ This capture is only marginally less popular than the main move  9...Nd7  . }
10. dxe5 Nd7 11. f4
{ This is one option. White could also play  11.Nf3  f6  12.exf6  Nxf6  13.Ne5  Nxe5  14.Bxe5  and enjoy his control over  e5  and the two bishops. }
