Qe7 9. Ne5 Nd7
{ In case of moves like ...Bd7 or ...Qc7 White can just continue with the plan of f4 e. g.  9...Bd7  10.f4   or  9...Qc7  10.f4  . }
10. Nxd7
{ The following counterintuitive tactical sequence is mostly why ...Qe7 was put out of practice in the early 2010s. White either wins or has the option of an edge + forcing a draw. Btw, the engines still can't find this idea on their own. }
10... Bxd7
{ What would be more natural than to capture with the bishop and connect rooks. }
11. Bxd6 Qxd6 12. dxc5 Qxc5
{ White has made three forcing and unintuitive captures in a row. Now the engines take a while, but eventually find it... }
