Qe7 9. Ne5 Nd7 10. Nxd7 Bxd7 11. Bxd6 Qxd6 12. dxc5 Qxc5 13. Bxh7+ Kxh7 14.
Qh5+ Kg8 15. Ne4 Qc4
{ The most played move. Only slightly different is ...Qb5 which attacks the b2-pawn  15...Qb5  16.Ng5  Rfd8  17.Qxf7+  Kh8  18.Qh5+  Kg8  19.O-O-O  . }
16. Ng5 Qd3 { Black tries to defend h7 from behind. } 17. e4
{ An important move, blocking the diagonal. } 17... Rfd8
{ Most natural, defending the bishop, but engines prefer ...Rfe8 or ...Rfc8 which just lets White take the bishop. }
18. Qxf7+ Kh8 19. Rd1 Qb5 20. f4
{ White wants to castle or bring the rook in with Rf1-Rf3-Rh3#.  20.a4  distracting the Queen in order to castle, is also possible. }
