1. d4
{ This was a Classical game. One of our heroes, Kamsky, was rated 2709, while the Super-GM and multiple time Chessable author Sam Shankland was rated 2611. }
1... Nf6 2. Bf4 d5 3. e3 e6 4. Nd2 c5 5. c3 Nc6 6. Ngf3 Bd6 7. Bg3 O-O 8. Bd3
Qe7 9. Ne5 Nd7 10. Nxd7 Bxd7 11. Bxd6 Qxd6 12. dxc5 Qxc5 13. Bxh7+ Kxh7 14.
Qh5+ Kg8 15. Ne4 Qc4 16. Ng5 Rfd8
{ Shankland protects the bishop, most humans will. } 17. Qxf7+ Kh8 18. Qh5+
{ Returning to h5. } 18... Kg8 19. Rd1 { Controlling the d-file. } 19... e5 20.
Qf7+ Kh8 21. e4 { Exploiting the pin. } 21... Ne7
{ The only way to put up resistance. If  21...Bg4  22.f3  Qc5  23.Qg6  Qe3+  24.Kf1  Kg8  25.Qh7+  Kf8  26.Qh8+  Ke7  27.Qxg7+  Kd6  28.Rxd5# }
22. Qxe7 Bb5 { Trying for a hail-mary mate. } 23. Rd2 Qxa2 24. Qf7 Qa1+ 25. Rd1
Qxb2 26. Qh5+ Kg8 27. Qh7+ Kf8 28. Qh8+ Ke7 29. Qxg7+ Kd6 30. Rxd5+ Kc6 31.
Qf6+ { Black resigned in view of  31...Kc7  32.Ne6+  . } *

[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
