[White "9. Classical Setup with ...Bd6, Main Line"]
[Black "9...Nh5"]
[Result "*"]

1. d4 d5 2. Bf4 Nf6 3. e3 c5 4. Nf3 Nc6 5. Nbd2 e6 6. c3 Bd6 7. Bg3 O-O 8. Bd3
b6 9. e4
{ Only the 4th most common move with roughly 3500 games, but the best-scoring try. The immediate threat is e5, forking Black's pieces, so Black has to react somehow. }
9... Nh5 { Very rare. } 10. Bxd6
{ An independent option. However, White could aso just transpose to the main line with  10.e5  Be7  11.Ng5  Bxg5  12.Qxh5  g6  13.Qe2  cxd4  14.h4  or just play. }
10... Qxd6 11. e5 Qc7 12. Qc2
{ Black's knight is stranded. After they defend the threat on h7 we should play g3 to further take away f4 from it. }
