1. d4 d5 2. Bf4 Nf6 3. e3 c5 4. Nf3 Nc6 5. Nbd2 e6 6. c3 Bd6 7. Bg3 O-O 8. Bd3
b6 9. e4 cxd4
{ The 4th most common move. I remember when you could first try to play Lc0 it constantly chose this line... }
10. e5 dxc3 11. bxc3 Nxe5 12. Nxe5
{ What piece should White take with? Taking with the knight is objectively stronger, but it's fine to take with either.  12.Bxe5  gets more pieces off and installs the strong knight on e5 after  12...Bxe5  13.Nxe5  Qc7  14.Qe2  Qxc3  15.O-O  with similar play to the text. }
12... Qc7 13. Qe2 Qxc3 14. O-O
{ Material is now nominally equal, but White's development lead and extra minor piece should tell after something like ...Bb7 and Rfc1. }
