{ The most common move, with 250 games, but bad. } 14. Rd1 Qc8 15. O-O
{ This looks like a moment for the gift like in the previous line and it can be tried, but since Black's bishop is open, the result is only a very slight edge, with best play. It's probably still the right choice in Blitz & Rapid. Here's how best play goes  15.Bxh7+  Kxh7  16.Qh4+  Kg8  17.Ng5  Rd8  18.Qh7+  Kf8  19.O-O  Qc6!  20.Nf3  the knight is forced to return  20...Ke8!  This is not very easy to find  21.b4  White gets his piece back  21...Bf8  22.bxa5  with a very slight edge to White. Therefore objectively strongest is to play on the d-file and on the threat of the b4 fork. }
15... Bxe4 16. Qxe4 { Now b4 is threatened. } 16... Be7
{ If  16...Nb7?!  17.Ng5!   or  16...Nc6?!  17.Ng5!  g6  18.Bd6! } 17. Ne5 Nb7
{ If  17...Bf6?!  18.Nd7! } 18. Nc6
{ This position has never been reached in the database. } 18... Bf6
{ One way to go badly wrong. Better is  18...Re8  19.b4  Nd8  20.Nxe7+  Rxe7  21.c4  With an edge for White.   or  18...Re8  19.h4  . }
19. Be5 { Aiming for the Ne7 fork! } *

