1. d4 d5 2. Bf4 Nf6 3. e3 c5 4. Nf3 Nc6 5. Nbd2 e6 6. c3 Bd6 7. Bg3 O-O 8. Bd3
b6 9. e4 Be7
{ Unintuitive, but best, stepping away from the fork and inviting e5, been played in ~1300 games. }
10. e5
{ The ambitious main move   10.dxc5  The slightly less ambitious move, but a good practical weapon to know about since it's quite rare, played only in ~30 games in the database. See the trainable lines. }
10... Nh5
{ The main move   10...Nd7  This retreat is not good for Black  11.h4  f6   11...f5  12.exf6  Nxf6  13.Ne5  Bb7  14.Qe2   11...h6  12.O-O  12.Ng5  fxg5  13.Bxh7+  Kxh7  14.hxg5+  Kg8  15.Rh8+  Kxh8  16.Qh5+  Kg8  17.g6  and mate is unavoidable. }
11. Ng5 { The most common and most dynamic move. } 11... Bxg5
{ Everything else is bad   11...Nxg3  12.Bxh7+  Kh8  13.Nxf7+  Rxf7  14.hxg3   11...g6  12.Nxh7  Kxh7  13.Qxh5+  Kg7  14.Qg4  cxd4  15.h4 }
12. Qxh5 g6
{ 12...Bxd2+  This turns out to be good for White  13.Kxd2  Now g6 can be met with Qh6 and h6 with Bh4 and g4. }
13. Qe2 cxd4 { This position has been reached in ~300 games. } 14. h4 Bh6
{ The main move   14...Be7  Another retreat  15.h5  Pushing on  15...dxc3  16.bxc3  g5   16...Kg7  This move is suggested by Georgiev  17.Rd1  Bb7   17...Bd7  18.Bb1  18.Bb1  White has a dangerous attacking position  18...Rc8  19.Nf3  17.O-O  Despite engines showing near equality, White basically has the sort of position he wants and Black's life isn't easy   14...dxc3  This line was tested twice in Rosen vs Kashlinskaya IM not a GM Speed Chess match with the result being 1-1, but it's otherwise basically absent from practice  15.hxg5  cxd2+  16.Qxd2  White's plan is Qf4 to Qh4, but he'd like to meet ...h5 with gxh5 without allowing the Q exchange  16...Qe7  Threatening Qb4  17.a3  White needs to figure out an attack on the kingside   14...Bxd2+  Also an option  15.Qxd2  dxc3  16.bxc3  d4  17.c4  Qe7  18.Be4  Bb7  19.h5 }
15. h5 { Pushing on. } 15... dxc3
{ 15...Bg7  16.Nf3  dxc3  17.bxc3  Transposes to below   15...g5  16.Nf3  dxc3  17.bxc3  Transposes to below }
16. bxc3 Bg7 17. Nf3
{ White has three good choices here. The text,  17.f4  and  17.Kf1  . See the trainable lines. }
