{ This was a Classical game. White was rated 2641, Black was rated 2531. } 1...
Nf6 2. Nf3 d5 3. Bf4 c5 4. e3 Nc6 5. Nbd2 e6 6. c3 Nh5 7. Bg5 f6 8. Bh4 g6 9.
Bd3 cxd4 10. cxd4 Be7 { This is Black's main move at GM level. } 11. O-O O-O
12. Rc1 Bd7 13. a3 { Prophylaxis, to prevent ...Nb4 and ...Bb5. } 13... Ng7
{ This isn't perhaps best. Giri-So saw   13...Rc8  14.Nb1!   13...g5??  This doesn't work without the Queen on e7 like in Krykun's main line!  14.Nxg5  fxg5  15.Qxh5  Rf7  16.Bg3  White's practically winning, being a pawn up and dominating on both sides of the board with many ways to strengthen the position and attack on the king, e. g. b4-b5, f4, Nf3 etc. }
14. Nb3 Nf5 15. Bxf5 { The knights on f5/f4 never survive long in GM games... }
15... gxf5 { 15...exf5  16.Nc5   16.Bg3 } 16. Nc5
