16... Bxc5 { 16...b6?  17.Nxe6  Bxe6  18.Rxc6 } 17. Rxc5
{ Both sides have traded a bishop for a strong knight, but the difference in the opposing bishops is huge. Black's bishop is doing nothing on d7 while White's bishop is pinning the f-pawn and will win the game. }
17... b6 18. Rc3
{ The rook is useful on the third rank. e4 is always a possibility. } 18... Na5
{ van Foreest doesn't sense the danger and relinquishes control over the seemingly protected e5. }
