1... d5 2. Bf4 Nf6 3. e3 e6 4. Nd2 Bd6
{ This is the main idea, Black challenges our bishop straight away. } 5. Ngf3
{ This, the Rubinstein-inspired and Carlsen-endorsed No Retreat! idea, cuts out all Black's trendy equalizing tries. Compared to the retreat with over 125 000x!, this has been played only around 11 000x. Black reacts in one of two ways, either they take the bishop off immediately with ...Bxf4, or they wait by castling. Other moves can just be met with Ne5 & Bd3, with more or less standard play, though with nuances, since White has the bishop still on f4. }
