{ 9...Ba6  10.Qg4  c4 could be played as well, but the text is even stronger, attacking the g-pawn. Now ...g6 can be met with h4 and ...O-O with Bxa6 and Be5. }
10. Bd3
{ White will castle and play c4 at some point, and can also later aim to play e4. Notice that ...Ba6 can just be met with c4 due to the pin on the rook. }
