[Black "4...O-O?!, 5...Ne8!?"]
[Result "*"]

1. d4 Nf6 2. Bf4 g6 3. Nc3 Bg7 4. e4 O-O 5. e5 Ne8
{ Overwhelmingly most common in practice. } 6. Qe2
{ Slightly unintuitive and good to know, given the host of other options White has. The point is to meet ...d6 with a quick O-O-O. Another move with a similar idea behind it is  6.Qd3 }
6... d6 7. O-O-O c6
{ Many of my opponents in Blitz have played ...c5 here which just drops a bunch of pawns but is still practically quite dangerous  7...c5?  8.dxc5  Qa5  9.cxd6  exd6  10.Nf3!   If  7...Nc6  White has a number of good choices like  8.Qe3  ,  8.h4  , and even  8.g3  , with the idea of Bh3. }
8. h4 h5 9. f3 { Aiming for g4. White can also play Kb1 first. } *

