1. d4 Nf6 2. Bf4 g6 3. Nc3 Bg7 4. e4 d6 5. Qd2 h5
{ The other h-pawn move, the sort you're likely to see in Blitz. However, it weakens the g5-square which becomes a nice outpost for a knight. }
6. h3
{ White can start by preventing ...Bg4. The point is to develop with Nf3 next. In general, in such positions White should always aim for e5. Of course, 6. O-O-O is also fine. }
6... c6
{ Black doesn't have a ton of reasonable options here.   Best might be  6...O-O  7.O-O-O   If  6...Nc6  7.O-O-O   If  6...Nbd7  7.e5!  this works now since the d-file is blocked and the d7-square is taken away from the other knight  7...dxe5  8.dxe5  Nh7  9.O-O-O   If  6...Be6  7.Nf3   If  6...c5?  7.dxc5  dxc5  8.Qxd8  Kxd8  9.O-O-O   If  6...e5?  7.dxe5  dxe5  8.Qxd8  Kxd8  9.Bxe5 }
7. Nf3
{ White has a healthy position with a lot of flexibility as to castling. Both O-O-O and plans with Bd3 and O-O with play in the center are possible. }
