[Black "9...Ne8"]
[Result "*"]

1. d4 Nf6 2. Bf4 g6 3. Nc3 Bg7 4. e4 d6 5. Qd2 O-O 6. O-O-O Nbd7 7. Bh6 c5 8.
Bxg7 Kxg7 9. e5 Ne8 { Another option. } 10. exd6 exd6 11. g4
{ White has a number of options here like Nge2 or h4, but this is best, stopping ...h5 and intending to meet a knight coming to f6 with g5. White is a lot better with a development lead and both Black's center and king as targets. Play could continue in several ways:   11...cxd4  12.Qxd4+  Qf6  13.Qd2   or  11...Nef6  12.g5  Nh5  13.Be2  . }
*

