1. d4 Nf6 2. Bf4 g6 3. Nc3 Bg7 4. e4 d6 5. Qd2 Nc6 6. O-O-O O-O 7. f3 a6
{ This seems like the main move at the GM level. } 8. g4
{ Here it is actually better NOT to play the thematic Bh6, even though that is also good. The text move has the advantage of preventing any e5 breaks for the time being. The other line goes   8.Bh6  e5  9.Nge2   Or  8.Bh6  e5  9.d5  . }
8... b5
{ The most natural and thematic move.   If  8...e5?  9.dxe5  dxe5  10.Qxd8  Rxd8  11.Rxd8  Nxd8  12.Bxe5  and White picks up the pawn again.   If the engine suggestion  8...h5!?  9.h3  and White has a nice advantage. }
9. h4 b4 { If  9...h5  10.Bh6 } 10. Nce2 e5 { Black gets his break in. } 11.
Bh6 exd4 12. Bxg7 Kxg7 13. Nxd4 Ne5
{ 13...Nxd4  is suicidal due to the pin after  14.Qxd4 } 14. h5
{ White will break through soon. Keep in mind that Alphazero has taught us that defending with  14...Rh8  never works because the rook will just get left out of the game after  15.h6+  . }
