[Result "*"]

1. d4 Nf6 2. Bf4 d6 3. Nc3 g6
{ This is actually Black's best move order. It can also arise when Black starts with 2...g6 and then continues with 3...d6. }
4. e4 c6 5. Qd2 Nbd7 6. Nf3 Bg7 { The most common move, with ~300 games. } 7.
Bh6
{ Thematic, forcing Black to make a choice. Marin doesn't cover it   7.O-O-O  Qa5  Marin's move  8.Kb1  O-O  9.a3  Now engines suggest this novelty. The idea is simply to slow down Blacks counterattack with ...b4 so as to be able to meet the move with e5! For example  9...b5  10.e5  dxe5  11.dxe5  Ng4  12.Nd5!  The thematic blow  12...Qd8   12...Qxd2  13.Nxe7+  13.Ne3  Nxe3  14.Qxe3  White has an edge }
7... O-O
{ 7...Bxh6  8.Qxh6  This is even better than usual since White is already more developed to where he wants to be while Black is committed to ...Nbd7. }
8. h4 Bxh6 9. Qxh6 Ng4 10. Qd2 h5 11. Be2
{ White will castle long and attack on the kingside. } *

