4. Nf3 { Controlling e5. Don't fall for  4.e4?!  e5! } 4... g6
{ Black can use this move order to transpose into a Pirc. The difference from our main lines is that we've been forced to play Nf3 and can't go for the plan with f3. }
5. e4 Bg7 { If  5...c6  6.Qd2  transposes. } 6. Qd2
{ We've tranposed to one of the previous lines. } *

