{ Black intends some sort of a Czech Pirc system with ...Qc7 or ...Qa5. } 5. e4
Qc7 { This is tried about as much as ...Qa5. } 6. e5 { We just push e5! } 6...
dxe5
{ The trickiest move. If instead  6...Ng4?!  7.exd6  exd6  8.Bd3   If  6...Nh5  7.exd6  exd6  8.Bg5  Ndf6  9.Bd3 }
7. Nxe5 Nxe5 8. dxe5 Nd7
{ Most natural. Best is ...Be6, but this hasn't been played  8...Be6  9.Qd4   8...Ng4  9.Bc4!  Nxe5  10.Qd4  f6  11.O-O-O }
9. Bc4 e6 10. Ne4
{ White has other options here like Qe2, defending the pawn. In every case he has a safe edge. }
