1. d4 { This was a blitz game in the Chess.com Speed Chess Championship. } 1...
Nf6 2. Bf4 g6 3. Nc3 d5 4. e3 Bg7 5. h4 O-O 6. h5 c5 7. hxg6 fxg6 8. dxc5 b6
{ Nepo gambits a pawn. } 9. cxb6 Qxb6 10. Rb1
{ Protecting b2, but now there is no option of castling Queenside anymore. }
10... Nc6 { Preparing ...e5 } 11. Nf3 { Stopping ...e5. } 11... Qa5
{ Pinning the knight and threatening ...Ne4 In another game between them in the same event Nepomniachtchi played ...Bg4 and Aronian went on to win in 76 moves   11...Bg4  12.Be2  Rad8  13.Ne5  . }
12. Nd2
{ A crafty move, blocking the pin, controlling  e4  and  c4  and maybe intending Nb3. }
12... Ng4
{ Black is trying to use the open f-file and get White's bishop. If  12...e5  13.Nb3  . }
