1. d4 Nf6 2. Bf4 g6 3. Nc3 d5 4. e3 Bg7 5. h4 O-O 6. h5 c5 7. hxg6 fxg6 8. dxc5
Qa5 9. Nf3 Nc6 { A rare move. } 10. Nd2
{ Trying to go to b3 to attack the Queen and defend the pawn on  c5  . } 10...
Qxc5
{ Black takes the pawn before it is too late. If  10...Nh5!?  11.Nxd5  opens the diagonal and leads to some interesting stuff. For example  11...Nxf4  12.Nxf4  Bxb2  13.Bc4+  Kg7  14.Rb1   or  10...Nh5!?  11.Nxd5  e6  12.Rxh5!  gxh5  13.Nc3   or  10...Nh5!?  11.Nxd5  Be6  12.Bc7!  Qxc5  13.c4  . }
11. Nb3 Qb6 12. Nxd5 Nxd5 13. Qxd5+ e6 14. Qe4 Bxb2
{ Black goes up material, but... } 15. Rd1 Bc3+ 16. Nd2 Nb4
{ Perhaps the trickiest move, intending ...Nd5.   If  16...Qa5  17.Bc4  .   If  16...Rd8  17.Bd3  . }
17. Bc4 Nd5 18. O-O Nxf4 19. exf4
{ The position is a bit messy, but White's better, being ahead in development and with the safer king. The engines give a continuation like   19...Qd4  20.Bxe6+!  Kh8  21.Bxc8  Rxc8  22.g3  with an edge to White. }
