1. d4 Nf6 2. Bf4 g6 3. Nc3 d5 4. e3 Bg7 5. h4 h5 6. Nf3 O-O 7. Be2 c5 8. dxc5
Nbd7 { A good alternative for Black. If  8...Nc6  9.O-O  and White is better. }
9. Nxd5 Nxd5 10. Qxd5 Bxb2
{ 10...Qa5+  11.Qd2  Qxd2+  12.Kxd2!  Covering c3!  12...Bxb2  13.Rab1  Ba3  14.c6  bxc6  15.Rb3  Bc5  16.Rhb1+= }
11. O-O { White just sacs the exchange for a strong bishop. } 11... Bxa1 12.
Rxa1 Qa5 13. Bh6 Qxc5 14. Qb3
{ Black should probably give back the exchange. If he doesn't White gets a strong attack by involving the minor pieces. }
