1. d4 { This was a Rapid game. White was rated 2609, Black 2456. } 1... Nf6 2.
Bf4 g6 3. Nc3 d5 4. e3 Bg7 5. h4 c6 6. Be2 h5 7. Nf3 Bg4
{ Black chooses ...Bg4. } 8. Ne5
{ The thematic knight jump. Also good is  8.Ng5  , keeping the knights on the board. }
8... Bxe2 9. Qxe2 Nbd7 10. O-O-O Qa5 11. Kb1 Nxe5 12. Bxe5 b5
{ Black expands on the kingside. Trying ...O-O-O won't work out well for him, for example, after  12...O-O-O  13.e4  Rd7  15.exd5  cxd5  16.Rh3!  with the idea of swinging over. }
13. Qd3 { Making room for the knight to go to the kingside. } 13... b4 14. Ne2
Kf8 { Black refuses to castle. } 15. f3
{ White controls  e4  and prepares g4. } 15... Qb5
{ Black offers a Queen trade which would leave him considerably worse. } 16.
Nf4 { Stronger was  16.Qxb5  cxb5  17.Nf4  . } 16... Qb6
{ Now Black backs out of the trade. Perhaps better was  16...Qxd3  17.Nxd3  a5  18.Nc5  , but White's still much better. }
17. Qd2 Nd7 18. Bxg7+ Kxg7 19. e4 { Also good was the thematic  19.g4  . }
19... dxe4 20. fxe4 e5 { Black gets his break in. } 21. Ne2 exd4
{ After this it is bad for Black. Better was  21...Rad8 } 22. Nxd4 Nf6 23. Qg5
{ Or  23.Nf5+  . } 23... c5 24. Nf5+ Kg8 25. Nd6 Ng4 26. Nxf7 Rh7
{ If  26...Kxf7  27.Rd7+  Kg8  28.Qd5+  would end in mate. Black threw in the towel here. }
