{ This novel move was recommended by Kiril Georgiev in his Fighting the London System against the Barry Attack. The only difference is that he is considering a position where White has played Nf3 and not Be2. However, with Be2 we control  g4  and threaten h5 so here Black can't follow his recommendations of meeting both 7. Rb1 and 7. a3 White can play for a quicker h5 and get an edge. }
7. Na4 Qa5+
{ If the Queen retreats White will just push h5 with the idea of h6. } 8. c3
Nbd7 { Georgiev's move. } 9. b4 Qd8 10. h5
