1. d4 Nf6 2. Bf4 g6 3. Nc3 d5 4. e3 Bg7 5. h4 h6
{ This is sometimes seen. Black intends to meet h5 with ...g5. } 6. Nf3
{ This is the best move here. Be2 can also be played, but the text is more fun. }
6... O-O
{ Most likely. If  6...c6  7.Qd2  with typical play.   If  6...Bg4  again  7.Qd2  . }
7. h5 { Welcome to sactown! One way or another we're sacrificing something. }
7... g5
{ Black persists with his plan. If  7...Nxh5  8.Rxh5  gxh5  9.Ne5  and Black is already in trouble. The engine gives  9...f6  10.Ng6  Bg4  11.f3  Be6  12.Nxf8  Kxf8  13.Qd2  and White is better due to his much safer king after  O-O-O  . }
8. Bxg5 hxg5 9. h6 { The key point! } 9... Bh8
{ Obviously not  9...g4?  10.hxg7  Kxg7  11.Qd2!!  gxf3  12.e4!  with a quick mate to follow. }
10. Nxg5
{ White intends h7+ locking out Black's bishop and f4, cementing the knight. Black is basically lost here. }
