{ The third most common move. } 6. Rb1 Qc3 7. Rb3 Qa5 8. Bg3
{ We keep the bishop. } 8... e6 { Black prepares for castling. } 9. Bd3
{ White just gets ready to castle and play Nc4. } 9... Nb4
{ This is very provocative. } 10. Be2
{ White keeps the bishop and intends O-O, Qb1, and perhaps c3 and c4. Nc4 is always an option as well.   Note that  10...Qxa2  lands Black in trouble after something like  11.O-O  d5  12.Bxb8!  Rxb8  13.Bb5+   Similarly,  10...Nxa2  and Black is too far behind in development after  11.O-O  Nc3  12.Nc4!  Nxe2  13.Qxe2  Qd8  14.dxc5  . }
