1. d4 { This was a Classical game. White was rated 2472, Black 2093. } 1... Nf6
2. Bf4 c5 3. e3 Qb6 4. Nf3 { Pechac goes for our fearless move. } 4... Qxb2 5.
Nbd2 Qc3 6. Bd3
{ Better is  6.Rb1  , but even here White's ample compensation is easy to see. }
6... Nc6 7. O-O cxd4 8. exd4 Nxd4 { Black grabs another pawn. } 9. Nc4
{ Always one of the key moves in these ...Qxb2 lines. The knight covers some key squares. }
9... Nxf3+ 10. Qxf3
{ White has a huge development lead for 2 pawns and is already better. Black has to be very careful. }
10... Qb4 { Black immediately blunders. } 11. Rab1 Qc5 12. Rb5
{ A fun move to play. } 12... Qc6
