1. d4 c5 2. d5 e6 3. Nc3 Nf6 4. e4 exd5 {  } 5. e5 Ng8
{ Objectively best, but oh so sad... } 6. Qxd5
{ We take with the Queen to develop it, follow up with Bc4 and prepare for long castling. }
6... Nc6 7. Bc4 Qe7 { The only defense. If  7...Nh6??  8.Bxh6 } 8. Nge2
{ Stockfish's nice novelty. Mostly people have just played Nf3 here. The idea is to cover the e-file and support Bf4, intending to O-O-O. }
8... Nxe5 { If Black doesn't take the pawn we follow up with Bf4 and Nb5. } 9.
Bf4 Nxc4 10. Qxc4 { White's threatening Nb5. } 10... d6 11. O-O-O
{ White's down a pawn, but almost completely developed and Black shouldn't survive this. }
