1. d4 c5 2. d5 Nf6 3. Nc3 d6 4. e4 g6 5. Nf3 Bg7 6. Bc4 O-O 7. O-O Nbd7
{ Fourth most common move, Black intends to occupy e5 } 8. a4 Ng4
{ Most played, with the idea of Ne5 } 9. Be2 { Anticipating Ne5. } 9... Nge5
10. Ne1
{ Black lacks space so White should aim to keep as many pieces on the board as possible. This is a very interesting idea since White prevents ...g5 which is a thematic move to clamp down on the dark squares.  Of course White can also play   10.Nd2  g5  11.g3  Ng6  12.Nc4  or   10.Nxe5  Nxe5  11.f4  Nd7  12.Qe1  is also good. }
10... Qa5 { This is hard to find. } 11. Ra3
{ White first defends the c3-Knight and then intends to contune with f4, taking over the center. }
11... Nf6 { Making room for the other knight. } 12. f4 Ned7 13. Nf3
{ White's space advantage is massive and Black has a very hard time even moving. The strategy of restriction can continue with h3. }
