1. d4 e6 2. Bf4 g5 { This tricky move has been tried roughly 800 times. } 3.
Bg3 h5
{ This is mostly tried. If   3...Bg7  4.h4  g4  5.e3  if the Dutch-like   3...f5  4.e4!  Nf6  5.e5  f4  6.Bd3   3...Nf6  4.Nc3   3...Nc6  4.Nc3 }
4. h4 g4 5. Nc3 { Or the direct  5.e4 } 5... d5
{ If  5...Bg7  6.e4   If  5...d6  6.e4 } 6. e4
{ Still e4! White intends exd5, Bd3, Nge2.   If  6...dxe4  7.Nxe4  Nc6  8.Ne2  Bg7  9.c3 }
