1. d4 e6 2. Bf4 f5 3. e3 Nf6 4. Nf3 b6 5. Be2 Bb7 6. O-O Be7
{ Normal play and the most common move here, with ~1250 games. } 7. c4
{ There is no need to play h3 here. } 7... O-O
{ 7...Ne4  8.Nfd2!  Aiming to play Bf3. See the model game Topalov vs. Paehtz Sr.   7...Nh5  8.Nc3  Nxf4  9.exf4  This structure is just good for White here. White will play Qb3 and centralize both rooks. }
8. Nc3 { Now Black has tried a number of moves. } 8... Ne4
{ The most common move at master level and also perhaps best.   8...d6  The most common move. }
9. Nxe4 Bxe4
{ 9...fxe4  This is about as common as ...Bxe4, but not as good.  10.Nd2  d5  11.Bg4! }
10. Bg3
{ Prophylaxis against ...g5, played exactly once. White will continue with Rc1, Nd2, Bf3 with a nice edge due to the space advantage. }
