[White "19. 1...e6, Dutch, Modern etc."]
[Black "Kjetil Lie vs. Lars Oskar Hauge, 2019"]
[Result "*"]

1. d4
{ This was a Classical game. White was rated 2531, Black was rated 2494. } 1...
f5 2. Nf3 Nf6 3. Bf4 e6 4. e3 Be7 5. h3 O-O 6. Bd3 b6 7. Nbd2 Bb7 8. c3 Ne4 9.
Rg1 { This is the position we reached in our trainable line. } 9... d5
{ Black adopts a Stonewall. } 10. g4
{ 10.Qe2  It was perhaps even beter to play this preparatory move first, to be ready for O-O-O. }
10... c5 11. gxf5 { White opens the g-file to his benefit. } 11... exf5 12. Ne5
Qe8 13. Qe2
{ 13.Nxe4  White could've already won here with this idea.  13...dxe4   13...fxe4  14.Bb5!!  Qxb5  15.Bh6  Bf6  16.Bxg7  Bxg7  17.Qg4  and Black has to give up his Queen to avoid mate.  14.Bc4+  Kh8  15.Qb3  Bf6  16.Nf7+  Rxf7  17.Bxf7  Qd8  18.O-O-O }
13... Nc6 14. Nxe4 { A move too late, but still good. } 14... fxe4 15. Qg4 Bf6
16. Nd7 Qf7 17. Bb5 cxd4 18. Nxf8 Rxf8 19. Bxc6
{ It's not clear this simplification favors White.   19.cxd4  White's just up a ton of material. }
19... Bxc6 20. exd4 Ba4 21. Qg3 g6 22. Bh6
{ 22.h4  Bxh4  23.Qxh4  Qxf4  24.Qxf4  Rxf4  25.Rg5  White just wins on material }
22... Bg7 23. Bxg7 Kxg7 24. h4 Qe6 25. h5 Rf3 26. Qe5+
{ White just gets the Queens off and wins on material now. } 26... Qxe5 27.
dxe5 Rf5 28. hxg6 hxg6 29. b3 { 29.e6  Kf6  30.Rg3  Be8  31.Ke2  Rh5  32.Rag1 }
29... Bd7 30. a4 Rxe5 31. a5 b5 32. Rd1 Be6 33. Ke2 Rh5 34. Ke3 Rh2 35. Rh1
{ White just gets the rooks off by force and Black throws in the towel. } *

